Plot pose-estimationÔÉÅ

Create pose-estimation visualizations from data within a SimBA project folder.

[1]:

from simba.plotting.plot_pose_in_dir import create_video_from_dir

[2]:

#DEFINITIONS

INPUT_DIRECTORY = r'/Users/simon/Desktop/envs/troubleshooting/naresh/project_folder/csv/outlier_corrected_movement_location'
OUTPUT_DIRECTORY = r'/Users/simon/Desktop/envs/troubleshooting/naresh/project_folder/csv/output'
CIRCLE_SIZE = 5
COLOR_ATTRIBUTES = None #Dict where animals are keys and color attributes values. E.g., {'Animal_1':  (255, 107, 198)}. If None, random palettes will be used.

[4]:

#RUN
create_video_from_dir(in_directory=INPUT_DIRECTORY,
                      out_directory=OUTPUT_DIRECTORY,
                      circle_size=5,
                      clr_attr=COLOR_ATTRIBUTES)
